  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nI'm issuing a transaction which fails with `SendTransaction` but not with `CallContract` on a simulated back-end.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.9.9`\r\nOS & Version: OSX 10.15.2\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nI'm expecting the `CallContract()`to fail when `SendTransaction()` fails as long as same arguments are used under the same conditions.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nInstead the `CallContract()`returns with an empty return array (even though the function has a single `uint256` return value (vyper).\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n```go\r\n// call (doesn't fail, err != nil)\r\nmsg := ethereum.CallMsg{\r\n\t\tFrom: fromFixed,\r\n\t\tTo: &toAddress,\r\n\t\tGas: gasLimit,\r\n\t\tGasPrice: gasPrice,\r\n\t\tValue: &amount,\r\n\t\tData: data,\r\n\t}\r\nreturnValue, err := bc.CallContract(ctx, msg, nil)\r\n```\r\n\r\n```go\r\n// transaction (fails, err = nil)\r\ntx := types.NewTransaction(\r\n\tnonce,\r\n\ttoFixed,\r\n\t&amount,\r\n\tgasLimit,\r\n\tgasPrice,\r\n\tdata,\r\n)\r\ntx, _ = types.SignTx(tx, types.HomesteadSigner{}, key)\r\n\r\nerr := bc.SendTransaction(ctx, tx)\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n-\r\n",
